### The `fantasy.AgentTool` interface

Each tool implements `fantasy.AgentTool` (from `charm.land/fantasy v0.38.0`). The two constructors used are:

- **`fantasy.NewAgentTool(name, description, handlerFn)`** — for standard tools
- **`fantasy.NewParallelAgentTool(name, description, handlerFn)`** — for tools that can run in parallel (like `web_fetch`, `web_search`, `fetch`, `sourcegraph`, etc.)

The handler function signature is:

```go
func(ctx context.Context, params T, call fantasy.ToolCall) (fantasy.ToolResponse, error)
```

where `T` is the parameter struct (inferred via generics). The `description` is a string rendered from an embedded Markdown template (e.g. `web_search.md.tpl`, `web_fetch.md.tpl`) with optional template data like `GhAvailable`.

---

**Summary of the architecture:**

| Component | File | Role |
|---|---|---|
| Search logic | `internal/agent/tools/search.go` | DuckDuckGo Lite scraping, HTML parsing, rate-limiting |
| Web search tool | `internal/agent/tools/web_search.go` | Wraps search logic into a `fantasy.AgentTool` via `NewWebSearchTool()` |
| Web fetch tool | `internal/agent/tools/web_fetch.go` | Wraps `FetchURLAndConvert` into a `fantasy.AgentTool` via `NewWebFetchTool()` |
| Fetch helpers | `internal/agent/tools/fetch_helpers.go` | HTML→Markdown conversion, JSON formatting, noisy-element removal |
| Param/type defs | `internal/agent/tools/fetch_types.go` | `WebSearchParams`, `WebFetchParams`, tool name constants |
| Tool registration | `internal/agent/coordinator.go` | Assembles all tools into a slice, filters by allowed list |
| Framework interface | `charm.land/fantasy` (external) | `NewAgentTool` / `NewParallelAgentTool`, `AgentTool` interface |

